 MBOMBELA – Trees were uprooted and parts of the R40 were flooded following heavy downpours across the Lowveld last night. Some parts of the Lowveld recorded more than 30 mm in just 20 minutes. Here is the rainfall over the past 24 hours, as posted by the Lowveld Rainfall Whatsapp Group. Strong winds uproot trees at The Grove: Trees were uprooted at The Grove. Reports of localised flooding on the R40 at Riverside came through at about 22:00 last night. Localised flooding on the R40. Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court was flooded. Nelspruit Magistrate’s Court. If you have more photos, please send it to stefan@lowvelder.co.za